          Internet access at the London meeting

Demon Internet Services Ltd, the UK's largest internet service provider, have 
agreed to provide 20 free dialup accounts for the duration of the London 
meeting. Demon have over 100,000 customers in the UK, providing full internet 
access for 10 UKL per month with local-rate call access throughout the UK.

The service provided for committee members will be SLIP or PPP dialup at 
33.6K - there is no shell account.

If you will be attending the London meeting and would like to be allocated 
one of the 20 accounts that will be available, please email me 
<sean@ocsltd.com> as soon as possible. I will provide details of the login 
script at the meeting or in email beforehand on request.
